$interpreted: Fatima: Esteemed ancestors, please heed our calls; shield and protect the Panther Tribe.

Fatima: Misty clouds and morning mist,
spirits from the ancient time,
twisted vines and witchy rhyme,
gathered here, intentions good,
to praise and pray for Whistlewood
Panther Tribe: EEE YA NA YA ~ HEY YA NA YA

Fatima: Dancing, trancing, prancing trod,
entrusting in the holy gods.

Flowers bloom yet pass in time,
our lives the same, our death divine.
With grace we thank you for our lives.
Panther Tribe: EEE YA NA YA ~ HEY YA NA YA
Miranda: (So this is the Inheritance Ritual...express the words in one's mind...)
Mother Liukanee: The ripe fruit of the Blessing tree symbolizes the blessings of the Panther God...
Mother Liukanee: Taking the juice and smearing it on the left cheek, this is the ceremony we carry out each year. But at the request of Cybin, this year...Fatima.
Fatima: Thank you for allowing this, Great Mother.
Miranda: Eh, eh? Me?
Fatima: Don't ask too many questions, come with me.
Fatima: ...Come. Do not move.
Miranda: Wah! So cold...!
Fatima: Okay, finished.
Fatima: The first blessing of the Panther God is for you, Miranda.
Miranda: Miss Fatima...why?
Mother Liukanee: Child, Fatima has told me. You are a human, yet protected Panthers even when they bore their teeth at you.
Mother Liukanee: The entire tribe all agrees that you are worthy of this blessing.
Miranda: I.......I...
Fatima: This is a gift, from us. You must accept.
Fatima: Think of it as a trade...bring the Holy Wooden Tablet back.
Miranda: ......
Miranda: ...Thank you all!
Miranda: Ancestors and holy spirits of the Panther Tribe, please forgive my blasphemous actions.
Miranda: I would like to borrow the Holy Wooden Tablet to be able to enter the tourney. Besides proving that I can measure up to the Beasts...
Miranda: ...I am undertaking this task for someone that means a lot to me.
Miranda: Panther God...please allow me to be tested!
